HEADWORD: Plenipotentiary
<hw>Plen`i*po*ten"ti*a*ry</hw>
<pr>(pl⟦ecr⟧n"⟦icr⟧*p⟦osl⟧*t⟦ecr⟧n"sh⟦icr⟧*⟦asl⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Plenipotentiaries</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL. <ets>plenipotentiarius</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pl⟦eacute⟧nipotentiaire</ets>.]</ety> <def>A person invested with
full power to transact any business; especially, an ambassador or envoy
to a foreign court, with full power to negotiate a treaty, or to
transact other business.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plenipotentiary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plenipotentiary
<hw>Plen`i*po*ten"ti*a*ry</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Containing or
